'''Spice spiders''' were members of a [[species]] of [[spider]] that could be found on [[Aaloth]],<ref name="Tempest Runner">''[[The High Republic: Tempest Runner]]''</ref> [[Taul]],<ref name="Phantom Limb" /> and allegedly on [[Kessel]].<ref name="Vandor">''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story: Tales from Vandor]]''</ref> Their webs were pure [[glitterstim]].<ref name="Tempest Runner" /> At some point prior to the [[Battle of Takodana]], a group of [[droid]]s stranded on Taul were ambushed by a swarm of spice spiders. [[Security droid]] [[PZ-99]] then sacrificed himself to save the rest of the droids, of which only [[C-3PO|one]] would make it off the [[planet]].<ref name="Phantom Limb" /> According to [[Fugas Fandita]], the spiders in the [[Spice mines of Kessel]] were supposedly attracted to light and could sense motion and fed on unwary miners.<ref name="Vandor" />
{{Species-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
Spice spiders were created based off of concept art by [[Ralph McQuarrie]],<ref name="SW-The Creatures of Marvel's Star Wars Comics, Part 1">{{SW|url=news/creatures-of-marvel-star-wars-comics-part-1|text=The Creatures of Marvel's ''Star Wars'' Comics, Part 1|nolive=1}}</ref> which was also the basis for the [[krykna]]<ref name="The Mystery of Chopper Base">{{Rebels|The Mystery of Chopper Base}}</ref> and the [[knobby white ice spider]].<ref name="Chapter 10">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 10: The Passenger}}</ref>

